cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cache-aided wireless device-to-device (D2D) networks and their optimization. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper considers channel fading effects and derives a network utility function. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper investigates the impact of individual preferences on network performance. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes caching policies to optimize network performance. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper considers the concentration of the popularity distribution of files, which is relevant to multimedia content distribution.
